Former factional chairman of the All Progressives Congress in Rivers State Golden Ben Chioma has resigned from the party. Ben Chioma is a strong ally of Senator Magnus Abe. The former leader of the Rivers State House of Assembly announced his detection in Port Harcourt on Tuesday. He said he is moving out of the party with his huge supporters having lost interest in the APC. Ben Chioma, however, did not announce the political party he would be joining next.